OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F465A1774868573
OL,3,CWelsh firm fined #2.2 million after
OL,4,Cworker killed in conveyor crush
OL,6,FAn investigation by the HSE found that
OL,7,Fthe company, which provides supplies
OL,8,Fto the building trade from hundreds of
OL,9,Fsites across Great Britain, had
OL,10,Fpreviously identified that employees
OL,11,Fwere accessing the danger zone within
OL,12,Fthe conveyor and placed signage asking
OL,13,Fthem not to do so.
OL,15,FBut, CCTV analysis showed that between
OL,16,FApril 14 and May 23 2024, operatives
OL,17,Fentered within the framework of the
OL,18,Fconveyor on 19 different occasions,
OL,19,Fthe HSE said.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G4/8
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,466,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46505
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F465A1774868573
OL,3,CWelsh firm fined #2.2 million after
OL,4,Cworker killed in conveyor crush
OL,6,FAlthough the company had placed
OL,7,Fstickers on the conveyor in a bid to
OL,8,Ftackle the working practice, no
OL,9,Ffurther action was taken to prevent
OL,10,Faccess until after the incident.
OL,12,FThe measures subsequently introduced
OL,13,Fto reduce the risk included guarding
OL,14,Fthe conveyor to prevent access,
OL,15,Fchanging the system of work so that
OL,16,Fthe pallets were unwrapped before
OL,17,Fbeing placed on the conveyor, as well
OL,18,Fas installing more CCTV to allow all
OL,19,Fangles to be seen by those operating
OL,20,Fit, the HSE said.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G5/8
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
